# Context
University students face a fragmented and inefficient internship search ecosystem. 
The opportunities are distributed on numerous platforms that have numerous interfaces, 
standards and communication styles. This fragmentation imposes a cognitive burden and 
creates decision fatigue, which slows the process by which students secure appropriate 
placements and undermines the early career momentum.

# Key Findings - Questionnaire
--> Low confidence in securing placements
    Average confidence score: 5.8/10
--> Difficulty finding suitable opportunities
    80% of respondents reported challenges indentifying internships that matches their skills, 
    location, targeted salaries and other requirements
--> Weak or Delayed Employer Communication
    Preferred communication is split, with 50% favoring in-app or asynchronous channels. Existing platforms
    rarely support this effectively, leaving students in prolonged uncertainty.
--> Logistical Barriers
    60% highlighted transportation and accommocation constraints, which are often invincible in current listings 
    and filtering systems.
--> Centralized internship listing system
    96.7% demands a centralized internship listing system.
--> Company feedback system
    83.3% want a company feeback section from previous employees or interns to discover the company culture.
--> Built-In Resume/CV Builder
    73.3% want resume/CV builder reflects gaps in professional readiness and unequal access to career tools.



